29/07/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Miroslav Lajcak met with BiH Presidency Chairman Haris Silajdzic on Monday (July 28th) as part of a series of meetings with senior political officials in the country. 
They discussed issues BiH should resolve in line with commitments stipulated in its Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU and requirements for the transition of the Office of the High Representative into the EU Special Representative. 
They also talked about the idea of holding a joint meeting of all party leaders to discuss current issues, including constitutional reforms. 
(OHR, RTRS, SRNA, Dnevni Avaz, Onasa - 28/07/08)
